# =====================================================================
# Frontend environment variables (example)
# =====================================================================
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and uncomment/edit values as needed.
#
# HOW THE API BASE URL IS RESOLVED (see src/lib/config.ts):
#   1. Runtime config fetched from /api/config (used on deployed Lambda)
#   2. VITE_API_BASE_URL below (used when running `pnpm run dev` locally
#      ONLY if you want to bypass the Vite proxy)
#   3. Empty string => same-origin relative URLs (DEFAULT, recommended
#      for local dev — works with the Vite proxy below)
#
# RECOMMENDED for local dev:
#   Leave VITE_API_BASE_URL UNSET. The Vite dev server already proxies
#   /api/* to http://localhost:8000 (see vite.config.ts). The frontend
#   will call relative URLs like `/api/v1/auth/register`, Vite forwards
#   them to your local FastAPI backend — zero CORS headaches.
#
# Only set VITE_API_BASE_URL if you want the frontend to call a backend
# running on a different host/port than the Vite proxy target.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000